      </p>

      <p>
        There are different ways you can take the money from your pension pot.
      </p>

      <p>You can:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>take a tax-free lump sum</li>
        <li>take your whole pot as cash</li>
        <li>keep your pot invested while taking money from it (<span class="tooltip" title="Your pension pot stays invested and you take money out when you need it">income drawdown</span>)</li>
        <li>buy a guaranteed income (<span class="tooltip" title="Gives you a regular income in your retirement">annuity</span>)</li>
      </ul>

      <p>You can use a mixture of all 4 if you want.</p>

      <div class="application-notice info-notice">
